{
  "texts": [
    "Unsupervised learning, on the other hand, involves the use of ML algorithms to analyze and cluster unlabeled datasets.",
    "These algorithms discover hidden patterns or data groupings without the need for human intervention.",
    "Common unsupervised learning algorithms include K-Means Clustering and Principal Component Analysis (PCA) (Hotelling, 1933).",
    "K-Means Clustering is a method used to categorize unlabeled data into different groups or \"clusters\" and PCA is a dimensionality reduction method used to reduce the number of input variables in a dataset.",
    "RL is an area of ML where an agent learns to behave in an environment, by performing certain actions and observing the results or rewards of those actions (Sutton, 1988)."
  ]
}